<subSubSection pageId="156" pageNumber="157" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="156" pageNumber="157">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="156" pageNumber="157">
Intricately branched spiny undershrub to 60 cm, stems finely adpressed pubescent, branches spinescent and with some stem spines near branch tips formed from old peduncles. Leaves sessile, 0.5-1.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.3-0.4 cm, oblong to oblanceolate, obtuse, margin entire, base attenuate, adpressed-pubescent. Flowers axillary, usually solitary, sometimes up to 3 in a diachasial cyme; peduncles 4-8 mm, woody, spinescent, bent at apex; bracteoles 1-1.5 mm, scale-like; pedicels c. 1 mm; outer sepals 3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm, oblong to elliptic, obtuse and mucronate, convex, pubescent with spreading hairs; inner sepals 4.5-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm, pubescent with spreading hairs; corolla 1.3-1.6 cm long, white, midpetaline bands adpressed pilose; ovary pubescent; style pubescent, divided c. 4 mm above base, stigmas 3 mm; capsule comose; seeds smooth, glabrous. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 70; 
<bibRefCitation author="Austin, DF" editor="Nasir, E" journalOrPublisher="Dept. of Botany, University of Karachi, Karachi" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" pagination="1 - 64" refId="B13" refString="Austin, DF, Ghazanfar, S, 1979. Convolvulaceae. In: Nasir, E, Ali, SI, Eds., Flora of Pakistan 126: Convolvulaceae. Dept. of Botany, University of Karachi, Karachi: 1 - 64" title="Convolvulaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Pakistan 126: Convolvulaceae." year="1979">Austin and Ghazanfar 1979</bibRefCitation>
: 12; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nowroozi, M" journalOrPublisher="Ministry of Jihad-e-Agriculture, Iran" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="1 - 110" refId="B244" refString="Nowroozi, M, 2002. Flora of Iran 40: Convolvulaceae. Ministry of Jihad-e-Agriculture, Iran: 1 - 110" title="Flora of Iran 40: Convolvulaceae" year="2002">Nowroozi 2002</bibRefCitation>
